SIMPLE: foliated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foliated
<hw>Fo"li*a`ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having
leaves, or leaflike projections; <as>as, a <ex>foliated</ex>
shell</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>Containing, or consisting of,
foils; <as>as, a <ex>foliated</ex> arch</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Characterized by being separable
into thin plates or folia; <as>as, graphite has a <ex>foliated</ex>
structure</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Laminated, but restricted to the
variety of laminated structure found in crystalline schist, as mica
schist, etc.; schistose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Spread over with an amalgam of tin and
quicksilver.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Foliated telluium</b></col>. <fld>(Min.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Nagyagite</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foliation</ent>⟦br⟧
